            <fr:addr>jms-00OI/14</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00OI/14.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Towards univalent reference types › towards models of iGHoTT"><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00OI.xml" title="Towards univalent reference types" addr="jms-00OI" type="local"><html:em><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2024-univalent.xml" title="Towards univalent reference types" addr="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2024-univalent" type="local">Towards <html:strong>univalent</html:strong> reference types</fr:link></html:em></fr:link> › towards models of <html:strong>iGHoTT</html:strong></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Slide</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>We have not gotten around to adapting the <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2022.xml" title="Denotational semantics of general store and polymorphism" addr="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2022" type="local">SGB’22</fr:link> model of <html:strong>iGDTT</html:strong> to obtain a model of <html:strong>iGHoTT</html:strong>, which is much more complicated.</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {A}]]></fr:tex> be a partial combinatory algebra.</html:li>
  <html:li>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\square ]]></fr:tex> be a suitable <html:em>internal cube category</html:em> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {PER}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {A}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {O}]]></fr:tex> be an internal well-founded order in the same.</html:li>
  <html:li>Then the category of internal presheaves of assemblies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [{\mathopen {}\left (\square \times \mathbb {O}\right )\mathclose {}}^{\mathsf {op}},\mathbf {Asm}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {A}\right )\mathclose {}}\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is expected to form a model of <html:strong>iGHoTT</html:strong>{}.</html:li></html:ol>
            <html:p>Impredicative <html:strong>HoTT</html:strong> via cubical assemblies due to <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/awodey-frey-speight-2018.xml" title="Impredicative encodings of (higher) inductive types" addr="awodey-frey-speight-2018" type="local">Awodey et al.</fr:link> and studied by <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/uemura-2019-types.xml" title="Cubical assemblies, a univalent and impredicative universe and a failure of propositional resizing" addr="uemura-2019-types" type="local">Uemura</fr:link>, <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/swan-uemura-2022.xml" title="On Church’s thesis in cubical assemblies" addr="swan-uemura-2022" type="local">Swan</fr:link>.</html:p>
            <html:p>Guarded <html:strong>HoTT</html:strong> via <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\square \times \mathbb {O}]]></fr:tex> due to <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/bbcgsv-2019.xml" title="Guarded cubical type theory" addr="bbcgsv-2019" type="local">Birkedal et al. (2019)</fr:link>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
